<div id="review_31831818" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/31831818" />
    <a title="Jim" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/695116-jim"><img alt="Jim" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1340192527p2/695116.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/31831818?book_show_action=true">Sep 02, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jim" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jim" href="/user/show/695116-jim">Jim</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/695116-jim?shelf=2fiction">2fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/695116-jim?shelf=western">western</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/695116-jim?shelf=1paper">1paper</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/695116-jim?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/695116-jim?shelf=historical">historical</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer31831818" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11042168792567579208">Not your typical good guy vs bad buy shoot &apos;em up western from L&apos;Amour. This is a little more thoughtful &amp; told in the first person, from our hero&apos;s POV. Bendigo journey&apos;s west with his older brother &amp; his family. They set up a new town in the wilderness. L&apos;Amour hits some of the high points of what that entails &amp; makes you think a bit about how hard it was for them.<br/><br/>Bendigo is a little to good to be true (typical hero) but it&apos;s a fun read. There&apos;s plenty of action, but not a lot of slap-leather,</span>
  <span id="freeText11042168792567579208" style="display:none">Not your typical good guy vs bad buy shoot 'em up western from L'Amour. This is a little more thoughtful &amp; told in the first person, from our hero's POV. Bendigo journey's west with his older brother &amp; his family. They set up a new town in the wilderness. L'Amour hits some of the high points of what that entails &amp; makes you think a bit about how hard it was for them.<br /><br />Bendigo is a little to good to be true (typical hero) but it's a fun read. There's plenty of action, but not a lot of slap-leather, get-out-of-town-by-noon stuff. Hunting for lost people in the snow, hunting for food, keeping out some riff-raff &amp; even a glimpse of NYC during that time.<br /><br />The only downside to the book is the philosophizing that Bendigo constantly shares with us. It actually wasn't bad reading as a teenager since it is idealistic &amp; appealed to me at the time. Now, it's a little too trite &amp; too much. Still, a very good book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11042168792567579208" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


