<div id="review_2764820657" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2764820657" />
    <a title="Maria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4486901-maria"><img alt="Maria" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1360532134p2/4486901.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2764820657?book_show_action=true">Mar 26, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maria" href="/user/show/4486901-maria">Maria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2764820657" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13786114294322136286">Five stars, just like all the others. And just like all the others. That’s why I read them! I&apos;m like Frances with her bread and jam--I always know what I am going to get, and I am always pleased. <br/>The young (I mean super young) love story was a little weird, but I’ll forgive it that because it also contained Louis’ prose at its best. I almost cried.</span>
  <span id="freeText13786114294322136286" style="display:none">Five stars, just like all the others. And just like all the others. That’s why I read them! I'm like Frances with her bread and jam--I always know what I am going to get, and I am always pleased. <br />The young (I mean super young) love story was a little weird, but I’ll forgive it that because it also contained Louis’ prose at its best. I almost cried.</span>
