  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2357144551" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2357144551" />
    <a title="Tate May" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/80248760-tate-may"><img alt="Tate May" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2357144551?book_show_action=true">May 09, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tate May" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tate May" href="/user/show/80248760-tate-may">Tate May</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2357144551" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6668995120962022134">The author Louis L’amour grew up in the fading frontier days. His grandpa moved into their little house and told stories to Louis about his time being a soldier in the Civil and the Indian wars. His uncles were also a big part in his life sharing their experiences. Thanks to the company of these men, Louis was first exposed to the history and the adventures of the frontier days that inspired his books.<br/> <br/><i>Bendigo Shafter</i> is a action filled novel with a lot of obstacles like harsh winters, Indian ra</span>
  <span id="freeText6668995120962022134" style="display:none">The author Louis L’amour grew up in the fading frontier days. His grandpa moved into their little house and told stories to Louis about his time being a soldier in the Civil and the Indian wars. His uncles were also a big part in his life sharing their experiences. Thanks to the company of these men, Louis was first exposed to the history and the adventures of the frontier days that inspired his books.<br /> <br /><i>Bendigo Shafter</i> is a action filled novel with a lot of obstacles like harsh winters, Indian raids, and the outlaws that drifted into their town that Bendigo Shafter and his friends have to face. When Bendigo Shafter and some travelers settle in a rugged Wyoming mountains, they quickly learn that they need to be depend on a toughness and wisdom many of them never knew they possessed. The resourceful widow Ruth Macken helped lead the settlers through the harsh winters, Indians attacks, and destruction of gold. Through all these obstacles, Bendigo is made into a man. When he goes to New York to reclaim his love from his childhood sweetheart, Ninon, he is faced with new challenges. Will all the challenges he faced help him serve in the big city? <br /><br />Benjamin Shafter is the best role model in literature. He is a man that people say you would want to raise their son to be. He is not a perfect man. He has some flaws but is a man that worked hard and helped others in an instant. He's a survivor and he doesn't give up easy. In the book, we are introduced to him as a young man who was physically strong. He is used to being responsible for others welfare, and was skilled with weapons that were necessary for hunting game for food and also dealing with drifters and outlaws that wanted to start trouble. When Benjamin Shafter got attacked by the mountain lion, I think the author was trying to show the readers that Benjamin could take care of himself when he gets caught off guard. I also think the author wanted to tell the reader that in the mountains, anything could happen. At the end of the book, Benjamin, Uruwishi, Ethan, Stacy, and Short Bull went to the medicine wheel and ran into trouble and were attacked by Shosshone, a younger indian that Benjamin had earlier saved his life. Louis was trying to show the readers that at the end of they day, Benjamin will do what needs to be done without hesitation. <br /><br />This book was a slow read at first, but made up for it with all the action and adventure it had. I really enjoyed <i>Bendigo Shafter</i>. It has been one of the better books I have read from Louis L’amour. I would recommend this book to people that like Westerns or action. This would be the perfect read for them or any of the Louis L’amour books. </span>
  <a data-text-id="6668995120962022134" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

